OL,3,CSunderland man becomes first to be
OL,4,Cconvicted of riot after national unrest
OL,6,FA Sunderland man has become the first
OL,7,Fperson to be convicted of riot
OL,8,Ffollowing violent scenes across the UK.
OL,10,FKieran Usher, aged 32 of Bramwell Road
OL,11,Fin Hendon pleaded guilty to a charge
OL,12,Fof riot at Newcastle Crown Court,
OL,13,Ffollowing unrest in central Sunderland
OL,14,Fon 2 August.
OL,16,FUsher was captured on CCTV wearing a
OL,17,Fface covering, encouraging others to
OL,18,Ftake part and throwing a missile at
OL,19,Fpolice officers. He was also filmed
OL,20,Fthrowing missiles at police as part of
OL,21,Fa large mob.
